public boolean sanityCheck(java.awt.Component gui,
                           int minSize)
Examines automata size.

Parameters:
gui - If gui != null, a JOptionPane shows the results and guides the user.

sanityCheck

public boolean sanityCheck(java.awt.Component gui,
                           int minSize,
                           boolean mustHaveInitial,
                           boolean mustHaveValidType,
                           boolean mustBeControllabilityConsistent,
                           boolean examineStructure)
Examines automata size and - optionally - some other stuff.

Parameters:
gui - If gui != null, a JOptionPane shows the results and guides the user.
minSize - Minimum size of the automata.
mustHaveInitial - Test requires automata to have initial states.
mustHaveValidType - Test requires that the automata are not of undefined type.
mustBeControllabilityConsistent - Test requires that an event has the same controllability status in all automata.
examineStructure - Test examines whether there are disjoint parts in the system. This method was originally in gui.ActionMan (to handle the gui-stuff conveniently).
